COMMENTS:
This is a basic, yet to the point short manual from Brooks Kubik (who wrote the excellent "Dinosaur Training" 

book), and edited by Stuart McRobert (the author of the ground-breaking "Brawn" series of books). It consists of 

a basic and an advanced course, however this manual is only 16pgs. long
Good read, but be aware that it is short, plain, and to the point, with no frills. 


COMMENTS:
Written way back, and it was as practical then as it is now and will be in the future.
It explains brief basic routines, using big basic exercises to build your whole body not just the arms, although 

if you stick to the routines outlined by Stuart McRobert you will build big arms providing your diet, rest and 

everything else is in order.
